2 Garlic
300 g Pork Loin Steaks
1 packet Mayonnaise
1 packet Honey-Soy Sauce
1 packet Jasmine rice
packet Garlic Paste
1 Carrot
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Soy Sauce Mix
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 tbs plain flour
1 drizzle olive oil
20 g butter
1.25 cup water (for the rice)
¼ cup water (for the sauce)
1 drizzle vinegar (white wine or rice wine)

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water (for the rice) and a generous pinch of salt to the pan and bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, grate carrot.
• Slice pork loin steaks into 1cm strips.
• In a medium bowl, combine pork and the plain flour.

• When the rice has 5 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, shake any excess flour off, then cook pork strips in batches, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes.
• Add honey-soy sauce (see ingredients), soy sauce and the water (for the sauce), tossing pork to coat.

• In a large bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar. Season to taste and toss to coat.
• Divide garlic rice and creamy slaw between bowls.
• Top with honey-soy pork, spooning over any remaining sauce.
• Sprinkle with crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy!